    <p>The <strong>National Electric Power Regulatory Authority (NEPRA)</strong> is Pakistan's electricity regulator that sets electricity tariffs for all DISCOs. In 2026, electricity tariffs in Pakistan reflect the cumulative impact of fuel price adjustments (FPA), capacity payments, and Quarterly Tariff Revision (QTR) determinations. This guide explains the current approved rates and how they affect your monthly bill.</p>

    
