    <h2>Protected vs Unprotected — The Most Critical Classification</h2>
    <p>The most impactful factor in your electricity bill is whether you are classified as <strong>Protected</strong> or <strong>Unprotected</strong>. This is determined by your <strong>6-month average consumption</strong>:</p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li><strong>Protected</strong> — average ≤200 units/month over last 6 months → subsidized rates (Rs 13.48–18.58/unit)</li>
      <li><strong>Unprotected</strong> — average above 200 units/month → full rates (Rs 23.59–48.84/unit from unit 1)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>At 300 units, a Protected consumer pays approximately <strong>Rs 4,800</strong> while an Unprotected consumer pays approximately <strong>Rs 12,500</strong> — more than double for the same consumption.</p>

    <h2>How NEPRA Sets Tariffs</h2>
    <p>NEPRA reviews and revises electricity tariffs through a formal process:</p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li><strong>Annual Tariff Determination</strong> — yearly review of base tariff for each DISCO</li>
      <li><strong>Quarterly Tariff Revision (QTR)</strong> — adjusts for fuel mix, capacity costs, and losses each quarter</li>
      <li><strong>Monthly FPA</strong> — monthly fuel price adjustment based on actual fuel costs vs. reference fuel costs</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Check the latest NEPRA decisions at <a href="https://nepra.org.pk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">nepra.org.pk</a>. Use our <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/">electricity bill calculator</a> to estimate your exact bill at current 2026 rates.</p>

